> It's hard NOT to love any ingredient when it's fritter-fied, aka covered in batter and cooked until perfectly golden. This version stars black beans, which we mash until creamy, then fold into a Southwest-spiced tempura batter and shallow-fry until crispy. They're served over aromatic cilantro-lime rice, then topped with a sweet and savory pineapple salsa and drizzled with smoky red pepper crema. Now comes the most challenging part of the meal: stacking a little bit of everything on your fork at once to create the perfect bite!

== Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. (TIP: Save the pineapple juice for adding to smoothies or cocktails!) Quarter @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Pick @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves and stems, keeping them separate. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Finely chop @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pineapple Salsa and Smoky Red Pepper Crema ==

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime juice. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine pineapple, tomatoes, half the cilantro leaves, half the shallot, juice from remaining lime, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

== Black Bean Fritters ==

Transfer beans to a #medium bowl{}; mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until almost smooth. TIP: It's okay if there are still some larger pieces.

Add @tempura mix{82%g}, @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, ¾ tsp salt, and 1⁄3 cup water; stir until thoroughly combined. TIP: Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if necessary.

Stir in cilantro stems and remaining shallot. Season with pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large, heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Add ¼-cup scoops of batter and lightly press down to form small patties. (TIP: You may need to work in batches.) Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in lime zest, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and remaining cilantro leaves. Season with salt.

Divide rice between plates and top with fritters and salsa. Drizzle with crema and serve.